fully completed over $6 billion in equity and debt financing secured by shopping centers, office, multifamily, retail and single-tenant net leased properties. In addition, Mr. Novick has also been an active real estate investor for the past 10 years, where he has focused on middle market transactions.</p><p>Prior to joining Estreich &nbsp; Co, Mr. Novick ran the investment sales department at Garrick-Aug Associates in Manhattan, specializing in the sale of retail shopping centers as well as single-tenant net leased properties. Mr. Novick has chaired multiple charity events benefiting The Lustgarten Foundation, raising awareness and critically needed funds for pancreatic cancer research. Mr. Novick is a member on the board of directors of the Jordan Matthew Porco Foundation, whose mission is to help prevent suicide among college age students. Mr. Novick obtained a BA from Syracuse University.\r\n                    </p><a id=\"toTop\"><img src=\"http://www.saratoga.demo/wp-content/themes/saratoga/images/back_to_top.png\" height=\"44\" width=\"41\"></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>", "About", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "2-revision-v1", "", "", "2013-12-15 05:20:30", "2013-12-15 05:20:30", "", "2", "http://www.saratoga.demo/2-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
