office, retail multifamily assets and developer selection projects for a myriad of clients. Prior to joining Ernst  Young, Matt was the Director of Acquisitions for Cohen Commercial Properties and American Commercial Realty.Matt is a graduate of Skidmore College, holds a Master s Degree in Real Estate from New York University and is a Member of the Mortgage Bankers Association. He is also a licensed broker in the state of New York and Connecticut.\r\n\r\nMatt has executed over 15 acquisitions/dispositions and 40 financings totaling over $800,000,000 in the last 9 years, of which he is the managing member of 3 of them. Day to day responsibilities will include sourcing acquisitions and overseeing execution of the asset management strategies.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"leader\">\r\n<div class=\"borderLeftbottom\"></div>\r\n<h2>LEN NOVICK</h2>\r\nMr. Novick is a Principal at Estreich and Company, a New York Based capital advisory firm that provides competitive debt and equity solutions to its clients. Mr. Novick has successfully completed over $6 billion in equity and debt financing secured by shopping centers, office, multifamily, retail and single-tenant net leased properties. In addition, Mr. Novick has also been an active real estate investor for the past 10 years, where he has focused on middle market transactions.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Estreich  Co, Mr. Novick ran the investment sales department at Garrick-Aug Associates in Manhattan, specializing in the sale of retail shopping centers as well as single-tenant net leased properties. Mr. Novick has chaired multiple charity events benefiting The Lustgarten Foundation, raising awareness and critically needed funds for pancreatic cancer research. Mr. Novick is a member on the board of directors of the Jordan Matthew Porco Foundation, whose mission is to help prevent suicide among college age students. Mr. Novick obtained a BA from Syracuse University.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"toTop\"><object type=\"image/svg+xml\" data=\"http://www.saratoga.demo/wp-content/themes/saratoga/images/backtotop.svg\">\r\n      <img src=\"http://www.saratoga.demo/wp-content/themes/saratoga/images/back_to_top.png\" alt=\"Back to top\"/>\r\n    </object><img alt=\"\" src=\"\" width=\"41\" height=\"44\" />\r\n</a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>", "About", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "2-revision-v1", "", "", "2013-12-15 07:27:10", "2013-12-15 07:27:10", "", "2", "http://www.saratoga.demo/2-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("26", "1", "2013-12-15 07:28:01", "2013-12-15 07:28:01", "<div class=\"row firstrow\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-11 col-offset-2\">\r\n<h4>STRATEGY</h4>\r\nWe capitalize on favorable economic and demographic trends for multifamily apartment complexes in the United States by targeting the middle market segment of select regions in the mid-Atlantic and Southeast United States.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row secondrow\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-3\">\r\n\r\nWe make select\r\n\r\nacquisitions by\r\n\r\napplying the\r\n\r\nfollowing criteria:\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"borderLeft\"></div>\r\n<h2>OWNERSHIP/MANAGEMENT</h2>\r\nProperties with poorly capitalized ownership and/or poor existing management personnel and practices.\r\n<h2>PROPERTY LOCATION, AGE AND VISIBILITY</h2>\r\nProperties in submarkets with consistent strong occupancy\r\n<h2>FAVORABLE MARKET DYNAMICS</h2>\r\nEconomic drivers (minimum of 2 local drivers must be present in a market in order to commit to an acquisition)\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row thirdrow\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-12\">\r\n\r\nWe enhance value and performance through operational improvements, systematic property upgrades, enhanced curb appeal and intensive asset and property management.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"row fourthrow\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-3\">\r\n<h2>LEADERSHIP</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-8\">\r\n<div class=\"leader\">\r\n<div class=\"borderLefttop\"></div>\r\n<h2>MATT MILLMAN</h2>\r\nPrior to starting Saratoga Capital Partners, Matt was a Vice President at Heritage Capital Group where he oversaw a 1350 unit multifamily portfolio in the Middle Atlantic with a cost basis of $96.ooM. Prior to joining Heritage Capital Group as Portfolio Manager in 2009, Matt worked in the Ernst  Young Transaction Real Estate Group where he advised clients on a range of issues such as debt and equity placement, acquisition and disposition of office, retail multifamily assets and developer selection projects for a myriad of clients. Prior to joining Ernst  Young, Matt was the Director of Acquisitions for Cohen Commercial Properties and American Commercial Realty.Matt is a graduate of Skidmore College, holds a Master s Degree in Real Estate from New York University and is a Member of the Mortgage Bankers Association. He is also a licensed broker in the state of New York and Connecticut.\r\n\r\nMatt has executed over 15 acquisitions/dispositions and 40 financings totaling over $800,000,000 in the last 9 years, of which he is the managing member of 3 of them. Day to day responsibilities will include sourcing acquisitions and overseeing execution of the asset management strategies.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"leader\">\r\n<div class=\"borderLeftbottom\"></div>\r\n<h2>LEN NOVICK</h2>\r\nMr. Novick is a Principal at Estreich and Company, a New York Based capital advisory firm that provides competitive debt and equity solutions to its clients. Mr. Novick has successfully completed over $6 billion in equity and debt financing secured by shopping centers, office, multifamily, retail and single-tenant net leased properties. In addition, Mr. Novick has also been an active real estate investor for the past 10 years, where he has focused on middle market transactions.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Estreich  Co, Mr. Novick ran the investment sales department at Garrick-Aug Associates in Manhattan, specializing in the sale of retail shopping centers as well as single-tenant net leased properties. Mr. Novick has chaired multiple charity events benefiting The Lustgarten Foundation, raising awareness and critically needed funds for pancreatic cancer research. Mr. Novick is a member on the board of directors of the Jordan Matthew Porco Foundation, whose mission is to help prevent suicide among college age students. Mr. Novick obtained a BA from Syracuse University.\r\n\r\n<a id=\"toTop\"><object type=\"image/svg+xml\" data=\"/wp-content/themes/saratoga/images/backtotop.svg\">\r\n      <img src=\"/wp-content/themes/saratoga/images/back_to_top.png\" alt=\"Back to top\"/>\r\n    </object>\r\n</a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>", "About", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "2-revision-v1", "", "", "2013-12-15 07:28:01", "2013-12-15 07:28:01", "", "2", "http://www.saratoga.demo/2-revision-v1/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
